				<h2>CNC: Linear motion without timing belt or lead screw</h2>
<p>Is it possible to build a CNC whose Linear motion system does not contain any timing belt(pulley) or lead screw(threaded rod).
I was wondering whether I could directly control the Linear motion by securing wheels of a slider onto aluminum rails &amp; directly connecting the wheels to a stepper motor.</p>

<p>The main objective of this question is to find the cheapest method for controlled Linear motion.</p>

