				<p><p>Interesting question.  Some degree of precision is required.  There are two ways to do this:</p>

<p>a) use an encoder associated with a wheel which reports the rotary position. That value is then related to the wheel circumference to obtain the distance travelled. Perhaps a wifi transmitter on each carriage would be more practical than wiring.</p>

<p>b) use an absolute positioning measurement system.  Your dimensions of 100m x 50m are very large and clearly any traditional belt drive/screw drive is impractical. As an example of absolute positioning, a laser rangefinder (+/- 1-2mm) at each corner would locate the gantry.  How a commercial product would be interfaced with the PID/control system is a homework exercise.</p>
